characters.name: John Snow
characters.AboutOfChar: Jon Snow, born Aegon Targaryen, is the son of Lyanna Stark and Rhaegar Targaryen, the late Prince of Dragonstone. After successfully capturing a wight and presenting it to the Lannisters as proof that the Army of the Dead are real, Jon pledges himself and his army to Daenerys Targaryen.

characters.name: Daenerys Targaryen
characters.AboutOfChar: Queen Daenerys I Targaryen is the younger sister of Rhaegar Targaryen and Viserys Targaryen, the paternal aunt of Jon Snow, and the youngest child of King Aerys II Targaryen and Queen Rhaella Targaryen, who were both ousted from the Iron Throne during Robert Baratheon's rebellion.

characters.name: Tyrion Lannister
characters.AboutOfChar: Lord Tyrion Lannister is the youngest child of Lord Tywin Lannister and younger brother of Cersei and Jaime Lannister. A dwarf, he uses his wit and intellect to overcome the prejudice he faces.

characters.name: Cersei Lannister
characters.AboutOfChar: Queen Cersei I Lannister is the widow of King Robert Baratheon and Queen of the Seven Kingdoms. She is the daughter of Lord Tywin Lannister, twin sister of Jaime Lannister and elder sister of Tyrion Lannister.

characters.name: Sansa Stark
characters.AboutOfChar: Sansa Stark is the eldest daughter of Eddard Stark of Winterfell and his wife Catelyn. She initially starts off with a very naive view of the world, but as time goes on and she and her family suffer one cruelty and betrayal after another, she becomes a more hardened and learned individual.

characters.name: Jaime Lannister
characters.AboutOfChar: Ser Jaime Lannister is the eldest son of Tywin Lannister. With Cersei's ascension to the Iron Throne, Jaime was appointed as the new commander of the Lannister armies but left the position to honor and help the North face the White Walkers.

characters.name: Margaery Tyrell
characters.AboutOfChar: Margaery Tyrell became Queen Consort through her marriage to Joffrey Baratheon, and later Tommen Baratheon. She was eventually killed along with her brother and father when the Great Sept of Baelor was destroyed with wildfire as orchestrated by Cersei Lannister to reclaim her lost power.

characters.name: Gregor Clegane
characters.AboutOfChar: Ser Gregor Clegane is a knight of House Clegane, the older brother of Sandor Clegane, and a notoriously fearsome warrior, with a tendency toward extreme and excessive violence.

characters.name: Sandor Clegane
characters.AboutOfChar: Sandor Clegane is the younger brother of Ser Gregor Clegane. After traveling as a fugitive with Arya Stark and having a close brush with death, he reluctantly travels with the Brotherhood Without Banners in hope of having a greater purpose.

characters.name: Drogon
characters.AboutOfChar: Drogon is one of the three dragons born in the wastelands beyond Lhazar, along with his brothers Rhaegal and Viserion. He is named after Daenerys's late husband Khal Drogo. He can be distinguished by his black and red colored scales, and red-black wings. He was also Daenerys's personal mount. With the deaths of Viserion and Rhaegal, Drogon is currently the last of his brothers, hence the only known living dragon in existence.

characters.name: Viserion
characters.AboutOfChar: The majority of Viserion's scales are cream, but his horns, wing bones and spinal crest are gold colored.[1][2] His teeth are shining black daggers.[3] His claws are black and sharp.[1] His eyes are two pools of molten gold[4][3] and his flame is pale gold shot through with red and orange.[3] Viserion has a roar that would send a hundred lions running.[3] Although his true color is cream.[5][6] he is often referred to as the white dragon.[4][7] He knows his name.[3] Wisps of smoke emit from his nostrils.[3] When wounded his blood glows gold and red.[3]

characters.name: Night King
characters.AboutOfChar: The Night King is the supreme leader and the first of the White Walkers, having existed since the age of the First Men. By extension, he is also the master of the Wights.
